explanation: The solution directly compares the lengths of the input strings. If they are equal, it returns -1 as there are no uncommon subsequences. Otherwise, it returns the length of the longer string, as the longer string will always have at least one uncommon subsequence. This approach is highly efficient due to its constant time complexity.

